This paper discusses challenges related to the management and preservation of evolving linked data, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several computer science sub-categories. Specifically, the paper addresses issues related to data modelling and querying, which are relevant to the fields of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Linked Open Data, which is a topic that is relevant to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a query language for modelling and retrieving evolving data, which involves techniques from the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
